snippet.textDisplay:
I'm gonna ask my Cantonese friends to cook me that real Cantonese cuisine, they got a restaurant a few blocks from were I live, they're really hard working people, I seen them start their business from ground up, they struggled a couple times with our local stumbling economy, cartel violence, a complete shut down of the plaza where they had their restaurant do to the company's holding the plaza bankruptcy, a massive riot to the mall where they had their new restaurant that lasted 6 to 8 months to recover the plaza and even endured the sickness of the mother head of the family (she is recovering and taking a long treatment).

While the plaza recovering from that riot, they really struggled to get back up, the father of the family cooked egg rolls and packed them in plastic bags of three egg rolls each, this man walked everyday to Walmart to sell his egg rolls in the parking lot, it was so sad to see them struggle. They got all their cooking utensils stolen in that riot.

They're doing great in the new plaza, those hard working Cantonese remind me to never give up, to always fight.

Greetings from Veracruz, México.
